<br>
First off, I agree with the &quot;it's fun to twink&quot; attitude. I love twinking and it allows me to try different classes at more levels. I leveled my first to 60 and sure in heck don't want to do it again the long way, plus the first 60 was different because there was a lot of exploration and learning that came with it which is the main reason for EQ, at least IMO. But after you know the whole game, or close to it, it would be too boring to level up the long way again, because there is no sense of adventure and exploration. Won't hold my interest.<br>
<br>
Now reasons Verant would gain from the &quot;nerf&quot;: and if they don't make a lot of sense, it's possible they aren't good reasons, but best I could come up with.<br>
<br>
1. People may stick with their main character for far longer...thus decreasing server population because of less twinks, but still keeping the money comming from the one account.<br>
<br>
2. Stabelize economy. I assume this post is also relating to EQ2 which I am also considering in this post. Would be nice to have a &quot;balanced&quot; economy when EQ2 comes out.<br>
<br>
3. Forces more people to learn their class better...thus creating a better more experienced high end game. Nothing like seeing a 55+ cleric cast CH on an umbuffed caster at start of fight and getting beat down because of it getting whole group killed, or having a 55+ Rogue twink jump in and start beating the crap out of the mob with no aggro control...thus causing rogue to die quickly and then have the group's damage output cut in half etc.<br>
<br>
There are more, but I&quot;m at work...all I could come up with at top of my head though.<br>
<br>
