That's like reading only the last chapter of a book that's been torn out of someone else's copy. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p align="left"><img src="http://www.blackarcana.com/camelot/sabmerc2.jpg"></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uglatius2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glatius2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/1/02 3:48:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23524.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: twinking</span><hr size=1> Twinking can be fun.  If you play a character to level 60 and aren't in a guild with constant raids, what do you do with the loot you invariably pick up?  If you play the game regularly then loot will come your way, particularly if you play in dungeons.<br>
<br>
Now there are some options.  You could sell all the stuff in your local market.  Of course if you're selling it for plat to someone who didn't actually earn the item, aren't you twinking them?  The only difference between twinking a level 40 stranger who gives you 4k plat and a level 5 toon of you own is the level.  And then you end up with a bunch of money in your bank account.  Whoopie.  What do you do with it?  You can save it for the super splurge on an item for 100k that you will never see otherwise.  Well, if thats your thing, good for you.<br>
<br>
Option two.  You could give it away to a friend, a guild mate, a stranger who crosses your path.  All of which are reasonable options.  I imagine being the server Santa Claus might have some positive karma attachted.  But aren't you twinking yet again?<br>
<br>
Option three.  You can destroy the item on the spot.  You won't use it.  No one in your group will use it.  Twinking is bad.  Let's just destroy it and move on....<br>
<br>
Option four.  You can twink a toon of your own.  You can actually get some enjoyment out that item that you and your group worked for.  You can get some pleasure from seeing your time having a return on it, albeit on a different toon from the orginal.  But hey, isn't the game big enough for people to enjoy it the way they enjoy it?<br>
<br>
Removing the concept of twinking means that once you have aquired everything you reasonably can for your high level toon, and assuming you're not in a raid oriented guild, you might as well put that toon on the shelf because few if any further rewards will be forthcoming.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ureztarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Reztarn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/1/02 8:36:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23524.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: twinking</span><hr size=1> Low level game isn't fun? <br>
